# Database & Environment — TruckBuddy / DeliveryAppBackend

## Primary database (all current work)

- **Heroku app:** `truck-buddy`
- **Database:** Heroku Postgres (production add-on)
- **App status:** Not public/live yet, but this is the **only DB in active use** since ~March 2026
- **pgAdmin:** Connected to Heroku Postgres for viewing/querying — not where Django scripts run

## Local PostgreSQL (not in use)

- **Server:** `DESKTOP-V9URLRP-PostgreSQL` / `localhost:5432`
- **Database name:** `delivery_app`
- **Status:** Exists but **stale / unused** — local refresh **TBD** (user decision pending)
- **Local `.env`:** No `DATABASE_URL` → `python manage.py` on this PC targets **local** `delivery_app`, **not** Heroku

## Where to run Django management commands

| Task | Where |
|------|--------|
| Migrations, seeds, `ensure_admin`, one-off fixes | **Heroku Dashboard → truck-buddy → Run console** |
| Local `python manage.py …` | Only affects **local** DB unless user explicitly sets `DATABASE_URL` to Heroku (avoid) |

Heroku CLI login is often blocked on this machine (Norton) — prefer **Run console**, not local `heroku run`.

## Heroku Run console — common commands

```bash
python manage.py migrate
ALLOW_DEMO_SEED=1 python manage.py seed_demo_data --force
```

## Seed / data safety

- **`seed_demo_data --force`:** Replaces only `demo.driver` / `demo.customer` rows — relatively safe on Heroku with `ALLOW_DEMO_SEED=1`
- **`seed_driver_vehicle_test_data --force`:** **Deletes ALL drivers, vehicles, and legal documents** — never run on Heroku unless user explicitly requests a full wipe
- Seed commands **refuse Heroku** without `ALLOW_DEMO_SEED=1`

## Agent guidance

- Assume schema changes and test data questions refer to **Heroku**, not local Postgres
- Do not tell the user to run destructive seeds locally when they mean to update Heroku
- When suggesting DB verification, mention **pgAdmin (Heroku connection)** or Heroku Run console — not local pgAdmin server unless local refresh is in scope
- Do not initialize or migrate local DB unless user asks to refresh local dev environment
